# The Rust BPMN conformance suite byte-compares these SVG goldens against the
# renderer's output (which always emits LF). Pin them to LF so Windows CI — where
# git checks out text as CRLF by default (core.autocrlf=true) — doesn't corrupt the
# byte-for-byte comparison. See packages/rust/kymostudio-core/tests/bpmn_conformance.rs.
conformance/golden/bpmn_svg/*.svg text eol=lf

# Same reason for every golden suite under tests/fixtures (mermaid_golden,
# mermaid_convert, sequence_{xmi,mdj,gaphor}): they byte-compare emitter output
# (LF) against checked-in goldens, and all fixtures are text. Pin the whole
# tree + samples to LF so Windows CI doesn't checkout CRLF and break them.
packages/rust/kymostudio-core/tests/fixtures/** text eol=lf
samples/*.mmd text eol=lf
samples/*.kymo.json text eol=lf
